{
  "texts": [
    "The random state experiments were performed with varying numbers of qubits n ∈ {8, 10, 12} and training set sizes N ∈ {5, 8, 10, 14, 20}.",
    "In Fig. 3a, we show the results for fitting random input states, together with the random and real label experiment outcomes.",
    "The empirical generalization gaps achieved by the QCNN for random states exhibit a similar shape to those obtained for random labels.",
    "Indeed, a slight difference in the relative occurrences of each of the four classes leads to improved performance by biased random guessing.",
    "We observe that the QCNN can perfectly fit the training set for few data, and then the generalization gap decreases, analogously to the scenario with random labels.The case of random states presents an intriguing aspect."
  ]
}